Generic single-database configuration.

Schema is owned by Alembic (not Base.metadata.create_all, not the old
app/migrate.py guarded-ALTER-TABLE script — retired 2026-07-04).

- Fresh install (no database.sqlite yet): run `alembic upgrade head` before
  starting the app — this creates every table from scratch. docker-entrypoint.sh
  does this automatically in containers.
- Existing install (a database.sqlite that predates Alembic, i.e. anything
  from before this migration): run `alembic stamp head` ONCE instead — this
  records the baseline migration as already-applied without re-running its
  `CREATE TABLE` statements against tables that already exist. The repo's own
  database.sqlite has already been stamped this way.

Any schema change from here on gets its own `alembic revision --autogenerate`
migration, applied via `alembic upgrade head` on every install.